# Run-crond daemon for KernelSU initrc service.
#
# KernelSU hooks init's read() on init.rc and appends the contents of
# every enabled module's initrc/*.rc file. This makes init treat the
# service definition below as part of the original init.rc — no file
# on disk is modified.
#
# The service:
#   - Starts after sys.boot_completed=1
#   - Runs as u:r:ksu:s0 (KernelSU's permissive domain)
#   - Is OOM-protected (immune to LMK)
#   - Auto-restarts on crash/exit (critical)
#
# For Magisk / APatch or systems where initrc injection is unavailable,
# service.sh falls back to running run-crond.sh via nohup.
#
# Notes:
#   - "disabled" so init doesn't start it before boot_completed.
#   - seclabel is set to avoid SELinux denials for cron operations.
#   - -1000 prevents the kernel OOM killer from targeting this process.
#   - critical ensures instant restart — no watchdog loop needed.

service dailyjobs-crond /data/adb/modules/dailyjobs/run-crond.sh
    class late_start
    user root
    group root
    disabled
    seclabel u:r:ksu:s0
    oom_score_adj -1000

on property:sys.boot_completed=1
    start dailyjobs-crond
